  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The investigators propose a randomized non-inferiority trial that compares preoperative
      Fluoro Uracil (FU)-based chemoradiotherapy to radiotherapy with a simultaneous integrated
      boost. In patients with T3-4 rectal cancer, the latter approach is considered preferential
      with regard to toxicity and cost. The metabolic response of the tumor, as assessed by
      18F-2-Fluoro-2-Deoxyglucose-Positron Emission tomography (18F-FDG PET) or PET-CT, will be
      used as a surrogate marker of cause specific outcome
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
