  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  histopathologically confirmed rectal adenocarcinoma with an inferior border within 15
             cm of the anal verge

          -  the tumor has to have evidence of T3 or T4 disease on Magnetic Resonance Imaging (MRI)
             or endoluminal ultrasound

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  unresectable metastatic disease

          -  Eastern Cooperative Oncology Group (ECOG) performance status &gt; 3

          -  patients not deemed fit for radiotherapy, capecitabine or surgery

          -  pregnant or lactating patients

          -  women with child bearing potential who lack effective contraception

          -  patients below 18 years old
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
